          "body": "update.test.ts lines 220-296 contain two tests that are byte-for-byte identical except for the CLI flag (--no-show-branding vs --show-branding) and the expected body value (false vs true). The 37-line fetch setup/spy/parseAsync block is copied verbatim. upload.test.ts solved the same problem by extracting runUploadCapturingForm(extraFlags). update.test.ts should do the same: extract a runUpdateCapturingBody(extraFlags) helper inside the describe block, then reduce each test to ~3 lines. Fix: add a helper function async function runUpdateCapturingBody(extraFlags: string[]): Promise<{url: string; method: string; body: unknown}> that handles writeToken, stubGlobal, spyOn, and parseAsync, then use it in both tests.",
